<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,685,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,685,710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This genus is distinguished by the following combination of characters: 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1100,1124,685,710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[1100,1114,685,710]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1.0">1</number>
)
</emphasis>
tarsal formula 
<number box="[1297,1313,685,709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
- 
<number box="[1321,1359,685,709]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4-5</number>
, metatarsus with basal segment elongate and at least as long as the two following segments combined (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[1253,1378,721,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[1320,1378,721,745]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[281,341,757,781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[360,383,757,782]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[360,375,757,782]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
)
</emphasis>
pronotum transverse, from one-half to two-thirds broader than long, base arcuate, pubescence usually short and dense, directed approximately straight posteriad, sometimes obliquely laterad, particularly near the posterior part of the median line and the base of the disc (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[858,1087,829,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[1027,1087,829,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1108,1131,829,854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[1108,1123,829,854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="3.0">3</number>
)
</emphasis>
antenna with last segment flattened, broad moderately elongate (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[580,809,865,889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[749,809,865,889]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[830,854,865,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[830,845,865,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
)
</emphasis>
procoxal cavities open behind; mesosternum short, projecting to a maximum of half the mesocoxal length, narrowly triangular and pointed; mesocoxae in contact medially (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[267,499,937,961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[439,499,937,961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[523,547,937,962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[523,538,937,962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="5.0">5</number>
)
</emphasis>
the labral chaetotaxy with the number of setae arranged in a pattern (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[151,211,973,997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,255,973,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[231,246,973,998]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="6.0">6</number>
)
</emphasis>
mandible with dorsal molar area modified to transverse rows of large teeth and with defined distribution of dorsal sensory pores (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[436,565,1009,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[505,565,1009,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,610,1009,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[588,603,1009,1034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="7.0">7</number>
)
</emphasis>
maxillary palpi 
<number box="[804,818,1009,1033]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="4.0">4</number>
-segmented, basal segment small, apical segment narrowly elongate and about half the length of the preapical segment (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[923,1052,1045,1069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[992,1052,1045,1069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1074,1096,1045,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[1074,1088,1045,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="8.0">8</number>
)
</emphasis>
labial palpi 
<number box="[1243,1256,1045,1069]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2.0">2</number>
-segmented and very short (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[277,403,1081,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[343,403,1081,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[423,447,1081,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[423,438,1081,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="9.0">9</number>
)
</emphasis>
ligula short, broadly rounded (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[791,916,1081,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[856,916,1081,1105]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[936,973,1081,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[936,965,1081,1106]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="10.0">10</number>
)
</emphasis>
labium with lateral pseudopores and prementum reduced (
<bibRefCitation author="Ashe" box="[356,485,1117,1141]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Ashe, J. S. (1991) The systematic position of Placusa Erichson and Euvira Sharp: the tribe Placusini described (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). Systematic Entomology, 16, 383 - 400." type="journal article" year="1991">
Ashe 
<number box="[425,485,1117,1141]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1991.0">1991</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[507,541,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[507,533,1117,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="11.0">11</number>
)
</emphasis>
male tergite 
<number box="[694,708,1117,1141]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="8.0">8</number>
with a variable number of small to large spines-dents (
<bibRefCitation author="Johnson" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Johnson, C. (1968) Notes on the genus Placusa Erichson (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae), with a key to the Nordic species. Norsk Entomologisk Tidsskrift, 15, 90 - 92." type="journal article" year="1968">
Johnson 
<number box="[151,210,1153,1177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="1968.0">1968</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[222,448,1153,1177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[388,448,1153,1177]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[469,506,1153,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[469,498,1153,1178]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="12.0">12</number>
)
</emphasis>
median lobe of aedeagus with narrowly elongate, appendage-like structure, rather loosely connected to the anterior bulbus between bases of parameres (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[933,1160,1189,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[1100,1160,1189,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1180,1208,1188,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[1180,1208,1188,1213]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="13.0">13</number>
</emphasis>
) flagellum long and multiply coiled basally (
<taxonomicName box="[439,602,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Placusa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tachyporoides">
<emphasis box="[439,602,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Tachyporoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) or short and inconspicuous (
<emphasis box="[1038,1169,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Canadensis</emphasis>
group) (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[151,211,1261,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[231,259,1260,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<number box="[231,259,1260,1285]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="14.0">14</number>
</emphasis>
) spermatheca simple, capsule small and approximately spherical, duct sinuate and sometimes with irregular posterior coils (
<bibRefCitation author="Klimaszewski" box="[375,603,1297,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" refString="Klimaszewski, J., Pelletier, G., Germain, C., Hebert, C. (2001) Diversity of Placusa (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae) in Canada, with descriptions of two new species. The Canadian Entomolo gist, 133, 1 - 47." type="journal article" year="2001">
Klimaszewski 
<number box="[543,603,1297,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
